ment between colleagues in the field of construction or architecture.','2024-07-14 22:45:56',NULL,105),(952,NULL,'2024-07-15 00:40:52',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'If you could take a vacation next week, where would you go?','',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,'If I could take a vacation next week, I would go to Ha Noi to enjoy its beautiful beaches and visit the ancient town of Hoi An. It\'s a perfect blend of relaxation and cultural exploration.','2024-07-15 00:40:52',227,106),(953,NULL,'2024-07-15 00:40:54',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'How long do you usually spend on vacation, and who do you go with?','',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,'I usually spend about a week on vacation, and I typically go with my family or close friends to make the most of the experience.','2024-07-15 00:40:54',227,106),(954,NULL,'2024-07-15 00:40:56',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'When you go on vacation, do you plan your time thoroughly or do you go without many plans? Describe your style of traveling.','',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,'When I go on vacation, I prefer to plan my time thoroughly to ensure I can visit all the key attractions and make the most of my trip. I enjoy a well-organized itinerary that balances sightseeing and relaxation.','2024-07-15 00:40:56',227,106),(955,NULL,'2024-07-15 00:59:39',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Where is the event being held and what time should I get there?',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,'The Employee Awards Ceremony is being held at the Rankin Auditorium. According to the schedule, you should plan to arrive at the Rankin Auditorium by 6:30 P.M., as the event is scheduled to begin with a welcoming speech at that time.','2024-07-15 00:59:39',228,107),(956,NULL,'2024-07-15 00:59:40',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,' As far as I know, the CEO is supposed to be the first speaker, isn\'t he?',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,'The schedule shows that the first item is the \"6:30 P.M. - 7:00 P.M. Welcoming speech (Tara Andrews, Vice President of Sales)\". It does not mention the CEO as the first speaker. So based on the information provided in the schedule, the event will start with a welcoming speech by Tara Andrews, the Vice President of Sales, rather than the CEO. Thank you for catching that detail.','2024-07-15 00:59:40',228,107),(957,NULL,'2024-07-15 00:59:42',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'I heard that two different types of employee awards are going to be presented. Could you tell me about the specific awards?',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,'The event will include both the \"Most Valuable Employee\" awards given out by the department heads, as well as the overall \"Employee of the Year\" award presented by the CEO himself.','2024-07-15 01:00:27',228,107),(958,NULL,'2024-07-15 07:39:05',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'Do you agree or disagree with this statement: \"A good supervisor listens to all the employees on his or her team.\"? State your opinion and give specific reasons to support it.',NULL,'I agree with the statement that a good supervisor listens to all the employees on his or her team. Listening fosters a collaborative environment, boosts morale, and helps identify potential issues early. It ensures that all team members feel valued and understood, leading to higher productivity and job satisfaction.','2024-07-15 07:39:05',NULL,108),(959,NULL,'2024-07-15 07:41:29',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'Some people feel that children watch too much television these days and that this is having a negative impact. Do you agree or disagree with this opinion? Use specific reasons and examples to support your opinion.',NULL,'I agree with the opinion that children watch too much television these days and that this is having a negative impact. Excessive TV watching can lead to a sedentary lifestyle, contributing to obesity and other health issues. Additionally, exposure to inappropriate content can negatively influence children\'s behavior and mental health. For example, instead of engaging in physical activities or social interactions, many children spend hours in front of the TV, which can hinder their social development and academic performance.','2024-07-15 07:41:29',NULL,108),(960,NULL,'2024-07-15 07:43:12',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'Do you agree or disagree with this statement: \"Advances in technology have made people happier than they were before.\"? Include specific reasons and examples to support your opinion.',NULL,'I agree that advances in technology have made people happier than they were before. Technology has improved access to information, making education and knowledge more accessible. It has also enhanced communication, allowing people to stay connected with loved ones regardless of distance. For example, video calls enable families to feel closer even when they are miles apart. Additionally, technological advancements in healthcare have led to better treatments and improved quality of life, contributing to overall happiness.','2024-07-15 07:43:12',NULL,108),(961,NULL,'2024-07-15 08:12:42',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'mechanic/ teach',NULL,'no1to5_6.jpg',NULL,'undefined',1,NULL,NULL,'<p>The mechanic is teaching the young apprentice how to repair the car engine.</p>','2024-07-15 08:13:33',NULL,109),(962,NULL,'2024-07-15 08:14:32',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'fix/ bicycle',NULL,'no1to5_7.jpg',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,'<p>The man is fixing the bicycle</p>','2024-07-15 08:14:32',NULL,109),(963,NULL,'2024-07-15 08:16:17',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'sit / at',NULL,'no1to5_8.jpg',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,'<p>The women are sitting at the table, enjoying their conversation.</p>','2024-07-15 08:16:17',NULL,109),(964,NULL,'2024-07-15 08:17:38',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'woman / suit',NULL,'no1to5_9.jpg',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,'<p>The woman in the suit is presenting a graph to her colleagues.</p>','2024-07-15 08:17:38',NULL,109),(965,NULL,'2024-07-15 08:24:16',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'<p><strong>Directions:</strong> In this part of the test, you will show how well you can write a response to an e-mail.<br>Your response will be scored on<br>• the quality and variety of your sentences,<br>• vocabulary, and<br>• organization.<br>You will have 10 minutes to read and answer e-mail.</p><p><i>Read the e-mail below.</i><br>From: James Parker, Office Manager<br>To: All employees<br>Subject: Moving offices<br>Sent: August 16, 2:35 P.M.<br>We are going to be moving our current office to another section of this building from Monday to Wednesday next week. I would like all staff members to be involved in this process. Please tell me on which of these days you can participate.<br>Thank you,<br>James<br><i>Respond to the e-mail as if you are an employee of James Parker. In your e-mail, suggest ONE time that you would like to participate and ask TWO questions about the move.</i></p>',NULL,'<p>From: Camaron<br>To: James Parker, Office Manager<br>Subject: Re: Moving offices</p><p>Dear James,</p><p>Thank you for informing us about the office move. I would like to participate in the process on Tuesday.</p><p>I have a couple of questions regarding the move:</p><ol><li>Will there be any specific tasks assigned to us, or should we just be prepared to assist wherever needed?</li><li>Are there any particular items or documents we should handle with extra care during the move?</li></ol><p>Looking forward to your response.</p><p>Best regards,<br>Camaron</p>','2024-07-15 08:24:16',NULL,110),(966,NULL,'2024-07-15 08:29:10',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'<p><strong>Directions:</strong> In this part of the test, you will show how well you can write a response to an e-mail.<br>Your response will be scored on<br>• the quality and variety of your sentences,<br>• vocabulary, and<br>• organization.<br>You will have 10 minutes to read and answer e-mail.</p><p><i>Read the e-mail below.</i><br>From: A. Chae, General Company<br>To: Fine Prints<br>Subject: Printing accident<br>Sent: May 2, 10:32 A.M.<br>Dear Fine Prints,<br>Your company recently prepared letterheads for us. However, I\'ve just noticed that you printed our old address by mistake. I have to send out hundreds of letters to our customers for a new promotion. Please e-mail me about this as soon as possible.<br>Thank you,<br>A. Chae<br><i>Respond to the e-mail as if you are an employee at Fine Prints. In your e-mail, make TWO suggestions for how to handle the problem and provide ONE piece of information you think will be useful.</i></p><p><br>&nbsp;</p>',NULL,'<p>Dear Mr. Chae,</p><p>I apologize for the inconvenience caused by the printing error on your letterheads. We understand the importance of having the correct address for your upcoming promotion and are committed to resolving this issue promptly.</p><p>To address this problem, we suggest the following two solutions:</p><p><strong>Reprint the Letterheads:</strong> We can immediately reprint the letterheads with the correct address and expedite the delivery to ensure you receive them in time for your promotional mailout.</p><p><strong>Address Correction Labels:</strong> As an interim solution, we can provide you with adhesive labels featuring the correct address. You can apply these labels over the incorrect address on the current letterheads, allowing you to use them without further delay.</p><p>Additionally, to prevent such errors in the future, we recommend that you review and confirm the address details during the proofing stage before the final print. This extra step will help ensure accuracy and avoid similar issues going forward.</p><p>Please let us know which solution you prefer, or if there is anything else we can do to assist you. We are committed to making this right and ensuring your satisfaction.</p><p>Thank you for your understanding.</p>','2024-07-15 08:29:10',NULL,110),(967,NULL,'2024-07-15 08:40:23',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'Directions: In this part of the test, you will write an essay in response to a question that asks you to state, explain, and support your opinion on an issue. Typically, an effective essay will contain a minimum of 300 words. Your response will be scored on • whether your opinion is supported with reasons and/or examples, • grammar, • vocabulary, and • organization. You will have 30 minutes to plan, write, and revise your essay. What do you think are the most important characteristics for a job you have had or you want to have? Use specific details and examples to support your opinion.',NULL,'<p>In today\'s job market, finding a job that meets both personal and professional aspirations is challenging. In my opinion, the most important characteristics of a job include opportunities for advancement, a positive work environment, and work-life balance.</p><p>Firstly, opportunities for advancement are crucial. A job that offers clear paths for growth keeps employees motivated and engaged. For example, in my previous role as a marketing coordinator, the company had a robust training program that encouraged learning and promotions based on performance.</p><p>Secondly, a positive work environment is essential. Working in a supportive atmosphere where collaboration and respect are prioritized greatly enhances job satisfaction. In my current job, regular team-building activities and open communication have fostered a collegial atmosphere, reducing stress and boosting productivity.</p><p>Lastly, work-life balance is vital for overall well-being. Jobs that offer flexible working hours, remote work options, and sufficient vacation time allow employees to manage their personal lives effectively, avoiding burnout. For instance, the ability to work from home a few days a week has allowed me to maintain a healthier lifestyle and spend more time with my family.</p><p>In conclusion, opportunities for advancement, a positive work environment, and work-life balance are key characteristics of an ideal job, contributing to both professional growth and personal well-being.</p>','2024-07-15 08:40:23',NULL,111),(968,NULL,'2024-07-15 08:43:43',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'Directions: In this part of the test, you will write an essay in response to a question that asks you to state, explain, and support your opinion on an issue. Typically, an effective essay will contain a minimum of 300 words. Your response will be scored on • whether your opinion is supported with reasons and/or examples, • grammar, • vocabulary, and • organization. You will have 30 minutes to plan, write, and revise your essay. Some workers must work at night. What are the advantages and disadvantages of night-shift work? Give reasons and examples to support your opinion.',NULL,'<p>Working the night shift has both advantages and disadvantages. One major advantage is the potential for higher pay, as many companies offer shift differentials for night work. Additionally, night shifts often have fewer interruptions, allowing for increased productivity. For example, IT professionals can perform system maintenance more efficiently without daytime disruptions.</p><p>However, night-shift work also has significant disadvantages. It can lead to health issues such as sleep disorders and a weakened immune system due to the disruption of the body\'s natural circadian rhythm. Moreover, working nights can strain personal relationships and social life, as night-shift workers may miss out on daytime activities and social events. Balancing these pros and cons is crucial for both workers and employers.</p>','2024-07-15 08:43:43',NULL,111),(969,NULL,'2024-07-15 08:45:58',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,'Directions: In this part of the test, you will write an essay in response to a question that asks you to state, explain, and support your opinion on an issue. Typically, an effective essay will contain a minimum of 300 words. Your response will be scored on • whether your opinion is supported with reasons and/or examples, • grammar, • vocabulary, and • organization. You will have 30 minutes to plan, write, and revise your essay. Some people choose to work at one job for a long time. Others prefer to change jobs frequently. Which way do you think is better? Use specific reasons and examples to explain your choice.',NULL,'<p>In today\'s job market, there is a debate about whether it is better to stay at one job for a long time or to change jobs frequently. I believe staying at one job for an extended period is more beneficial due to stability, professional growth, and strong relationships.</p><p>Firstly, staying at one job provides stability. A stable job offers a predictable income, essential for financial security and planning. Long-term employees often receive benefits such as health insurance, retirement plans, and paid leave, which are crucial for overall well-being.</p><p>Secondly, long-term employment fosters professional growth. Employees who stay with a company for many years can gain in-depth knowledge and expertise. They are more likely to receive promotions and leadership roles. For example, a software engineer who stays with a tech company can advance from junior to senior positions and eventually to management.</p><p>While changing jobs frequently can offer diverse experiences and skillsets, the benefits of long-term employment in terms of stability, professional growth, and relationships are more substantial. Therefore, staying at one job for a long time is a better choice for most people.</p>','2024-07-15 08:45:58',NULL,111);
